cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT

The paper deals with logic and graph theory, which are topics covered in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The focus on regular and biregular graphs suggests that cs.GT is a likely category, while the use of logic and counting quantifiers points towards cs.LO and cs.CC. The paper's emphasis on the spectra of first-order logic sentences also aligns with cs.DM and cs.CC.
